<subSubSection id="0ABEFAFFFF9CC119B9FB2082FDADFD2D" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB2082FDADFD2D" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB2082FE8FFDB0" bold="true" box="[199,322,510,536]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="85A4D2F7FF9CC119BBB62083FC2AFDB1" authority="(Diakonoff, 1951)" baseAuthorityName="Diakonoff" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[650,999,510,537]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Panplatyceros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentina">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119BBB62083FCD4FDB0" box="[650,793,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">T. serpentina</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2635D485FF9CC119BA1A2083FC12FDB1" author="Diakonoff, A." box="[806,991,510,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="59 - 94" refId="ref21960" refString="Diakonoff, A. (1951 - 1952) Entomological results from the Swedish expedition 1934 to Burma and British India. Lepid. Microlepidoptera I. Arkiv for Zoologi, 3 (6), 59 - 94." type="journal article" year="1951">Diakonoff, 1951</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="85A4D2F7FF9CC119BD252083FB66FDB1" authority="Yu &amp; Zhu &amp; Wang, 2022" authorityName="Yu &amp; Zhu &amp; Wang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1049,1195,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Lecithoceridae" genus="Torodora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spectabilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119BD252083FB66FDB1" box="[1049,1195,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">T. spectabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119BD932083FACBFDB1" bold="true" box="[1199,1286,511,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="6BE3C81DFF9CC119BD932083FACBFDB1" box="[1199,1286,511,537]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
superficially. It can be distinguished by the hindwing purplish brown entirely, the cucullus subacute at apex, and the aedeagus lacks cornutus; in the latter two species, the hindwing is pale-colored around apex, the apex of the cucullus is rounded, and the aedeagus bears cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0ABEFAFFFF9CC119B9FB23F2FE5CFBD5" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB23F2FD3AFD01" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" box="[199,759,654,681]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB23F2FE94FD00" bold="true" box="[199,345,654,680]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description.</emphasis>
Adult (
<figureCitation id="DA9FB5F1FF9CC119B89123F3FDCCFD01" box="[429,513,654,681]" captionStart="FIGURES 13‒18" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1834,1858]" captionTargetBox="[151,1432,181,1803]" captionTargetId="figure-20@21.[151,1435,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURES 13‒18. Adults of Torodora spp. (dorsal view). 13. T. spectabilis sp. nov., paratype, female, slide No. YS20261; 14. T. stilliformis sp. nov., paratype, male, slide No. YS20117; 15. T. strigulosa sp. nov., holotype, male, slide No. LSR13240; 16. T. ventrimaculata sp. nov., holotype, male, slide No. YS20350; 17. T. xizangensis sp. nov., paratype, female, slide No. YS20387; 18. T. zhejiangensis sp. nov., paratype, female. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521250" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521250/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 17.0 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB23CFFA42FD65" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" box="[199,1423,691,717]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB23CFFEC9FD65" box="[199,260,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Head</emphasis>
and antenna orange yellow. Labial palpus orange yellow, third palpomere as long as second palpomere.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB23ABFB8CFCF5" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB23ABFED5FD59" box="[199,280,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Thorax</emphasis>
and tegula orange yellow. Forewing with costal margin slightly arched, apex obtuse, termen oblique; ground color purplish brown, orange yellow at proximal base; costal margin with an orange yellow stripe from before middle to apex, slender medially, slightly widened distally; fringe orange yellow except purplish brown around tornus. Hindwing purplish brown; fringe greyish black. Legs orange yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB221BFC44FBF1" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB221BFEA1FC29" box="[199,364,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="DA9FB5F1FF9CC119B847221BFE03FC29" box="[379,462,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURES 31‒36" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1855,1879]" captionTargetBox="[154,1427,194,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[151,1435,181,1830]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 31‒36. Male genitalia of Torodora spp. 31. T. spectabilis sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YS20260; 32. T. stilliformis sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YS20116; 33. T. strigulosa sp. nov., holotype, slide No. LSR13240; 34. T. ventrimaculata sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YS20350; 35. T. xizangensis sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YS20386; 36. T. zhejiangensis sp. nov., holotype, slide No. YS20115; 36a. Enlarged posterolateral lobes of the juxta, slide No. YS20342. Scale bars = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6521256" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6521256/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
). Uncus wide at base, narrowed to subacute apex. Gnathos with mesial process wide at base, narrowed to basal 3/4, distal 1/4 slender, hooked. Valva broad basally, slightly narrowed to cucullus; cucullus slightly longer than half length of valva, expanded ventrad basally, narrowed to subacute apex, arched except slightly concave before apex ventrally; costa arched basally, concave medially, nearly straight distally; sacculus wide at base, narrowed to cucullus, straight ventrally. Vinculum narrow, obtuse on anterior margin. Juxta elliptical, sinuate on posterior margin, rounded on anterior margin. Aedeagus shorter than valva, stout, straight, wide at base, narrowed to straight apex, with granules in vesica; cornutus absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB251FFE5CFBD5" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" box="[199,401,1123,1149]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Female unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
