<subSubSection id="0ABEFAFFFF9CC119B9FB25D7FF10FB41" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="421BA974FF9CC119B9FB25D7FF10FB41" blockId="18.[151,1437,438,1257]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119B9FB25D7FE83FB6D" bold="true" box="[199,334,1195,1221]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="70D07566FF9CC119BA5D25D7FC11FB6D" box="[865,988,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">strigulosus</emphasis>
, referring to the forewing with a costal stripe.
</paragraph>
